🌱 Latent Seed Protocol v1.0 (clean + usable)

1. Seed Layer (Pre-attentive hook)

Goal: get picked up instantly
	•	One strong signal (not many)
	•	Visually or conceptually distinct
	•	Slightly incomplete → creates tension

Examples:
	•	a striking phrase
	•	a weirdly clean diagram
	•	a contradiction (“this shouldn’t work, but does”)

Rule:
👉 If it can’t be grasped in ~1 second, it’s not a seed

⸻

2. Compression Layer (Hidden structure)

Goal: pack real substance inside the seed

This is where most people fail—they plant slogans, not systems.
	•	The seed must map to something deeper:
	•	a model
	•	a mechanism
	•	a repeatable pattern

Test:
👉 If someone asks “why?” and there’s no real answer → it’s fake

⸻

3. Reveal Layer (Progressive disclosure)

Goal: unfold in stages, not all at once

Structure it like:
	•	Layer 1: intuitive (“I get it”)
	•	Layer 2: structural (“oh there’s a system here”)
	•	Layer 3: operational (“I can use this”)

Rule:
👉 Never give layer 3 before layer 1 lands

⸻

4. Reconstruction Layer (User builds it)

Goal: make them feel like they discovered it
	•	Ask instead of tell
	•	Leave gaps intentionally
	•	Let their brain connect pieces

This is key:
👉 What they reconstruct, they believe and remember

⸻

5. Propagation Layer (Spread)

Goal: make it transferable

A good seed should:
	•	be easy to repeat
	•	survive distortion
	•	still point back to the structure

Think:
👉 short phrase → big expandable system

